==English==

===Pronunciation===
*/bɔrk/, /bOrk/

=== Verb, Sense 1 ===
{{en-verb}}
# To misconfigure, especially a computer or other complex device.
# To break or damage.
# To snub or disrespect.

==== Etymology ====
[[Category:Disputed etymologies]] Possibly derived from ''[[borken]]'', which is an intentional misspelling of the word ''[[broken]]''.  ''The computer is borken''.  The word is often used in [[irony|ironic]] or [[humor]]ous contexts.

=== Verb, Sense 2 ===
# (''US politics'') to defeat a judicial nomination through a concerted attack on the nominee's character, background and philosophy.

==== Etymology ====
From the 1987 United States Supreme Court nomination of Robert Bork. [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_Bork#.22Bork.22_as_a_verb] [http://www.iht.com/articles/1993/01/13/topi_3.php]

